TA LI S Moreover, across TALIS countries, teachers with less than five years' experience are more likely than experienced 
teachers to teach in rural areas, where schools often have fewer resources. TALIS shows that teachers' self-efficacy 
generally increases over time. Although new teachers tend to be less confident in their teaching abilities than 
their more experienced colleagues, they often face more challenging work environments. Experience takes time to 
accumulate, but confidence can be boosted through participation in professional development, such as induction 
programmes and mentoring. Figure 1 @BULLET Difference between more experienced and new teachers teaching in schools 
