What this means in practice For many countries, participation in mentoring programmes is also lower than access, partly because not every 
teacher will have a mentor and some may serve as mentors themselves. However, even when taking this into account 
the difference between access and participation is considerable in some countries. For example, in the Netherlands, 
71% of all teachers work in schools with reported mentoring programmes, while only 17% report having a mentor. 